<asp:Content ID="FAQContent" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" runat="Server">
    <div class="aboutUsPage">
        <p>
            <b>Q1.</b> If I register for an account, what can I do?<br />
            <b>A:</b> Dear customer, once you registered, you can have the right to
            view all the pages of our website to help you make decision that which city
            you prefer to visit.
            <br />
            <b>Q2.</b> What kind of services does your company provide?<br />
            <b>A2:</b> Dear customer, once you decide which cities you prefer to go, you can contact us
            through the email or the telephone to book for a trip and we will provide you a plan
             of the trip.<br />
            <b>Q3.</b> When I registered an account, why the page always told me to enter a valid date?<br />
            <b>A3:</b> Dear customer, when you enter the departure date and the return date, please make sure the form
            is like the following example: 01-01-2016. This means January the first of 2016.<br />
            <b>Q4.</b> When I enter my email address in the registration form, why the page always told me to enter
            a valid eamil address?<br />
            <b>A4:</b> Dear customer, the email address could only be the format like "xxxx.xxxx@xxx.xxx.xxx". 
            Please make sure you did not enter any other signs. For example, "+".<br />
            <b>Q5.</b> When I want to go to the registration page why it always push me to the log in page?<br />
            <b>A5:</b> Dear customer, without logging in, you cannot view the other pages except the home page. 
            Thank you!
        </p>
    </div>
</asp:Content>
